Explanation:

- The GET /v1/posts/{post}/comments endpoint is implemented by PostCommentController@index. The controller returns CommentResource::collection($post->comments()->with('author')->latest()->paginate($request->input('limit', 20))).
- That means the response is a paginated resource collection (Laravel paginator + resource collection). The top-level JSON uses the standard Laravel resource collection pagination shape: keys "data", "links", and "meta".
- The "data" array contains serialized Comment resources. The Comment resource (app/Http/Resources/Comment.php) exposes these fields:
  - id (integer)
  - content (string)
  - posted_at (ISO 8601 datetime string)
  - humanized_posted_at (string)
  - author_id (integer)
  - post_id (integer)
  - author_name (string)
  - author_url (string, route URL)
  - can_delete (boolean)
- The pagination "links" object includes first, last, prev, next (URLs or null).
- The pagination "meta" object includes common pagination metadata: current_page, from, last_page, links (array of {url, label, active}), path (URL), per_page, to, total.

